Write a Row-Level Formula

Get the Most Out of Row-Level Formulas: Tips, Limits, and Limitations

Required Editions and User Permissions
Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
Enhanced Folder Sharing

User Permissions Needed
To create, edit, and delete formulas in private reports:
Enhanced Folder Sharing
Create and Customize Reports
Report Builder OR Report Builder (Lightning Experience)

Row-Level Formula Limits
Each report supports 1 row-level formula.
Each row-level formula can reference up to 5 unique fields.
You can't use row-level formulas for:
Cross filters
Buckets
Row-Level Formula Restrictions
Can't reference: Bucket fields, Summary formulas, Other row-level formulas
Don't support: Boolean, Timeonly, Email, Phone, Multiselect picklist, Due Date, Birthdate, Billing Address

Reporting Snapshots and Joined Reports
Reporting snapshots don't support row-level formula fields.
You can't create, edit or delete row-level formulas from the Fields panel. Create, edit or delete them from the OUTLINE panel.

Row-Level Formulas Aren't Available in:
Salesforce Classic
Apex API
title: Maximizing Row-Level Formulas in Salesforce
